Cook bacon in 12 inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, 4 minutes or until crisp. Remove bacon and reserve 2 tablespoons drippings. Season chicken, if desired, with salt and black pepper. Cook chicken in reserved drippings over medium-high heat, turning once and sprinkling with cheese, 6 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked. Remove chicken from skillet and keep warm. Add spinach and garlic into same skillet and cook, stirring frequently, 2 minutes or until spinach is wilted. Evenly spoon hot sauce onto serving plates. Top with spinach, then chicken and bacon. Garnish, if desired, with additional cheese.